data_sanity_check = data[[sanity_dict[data['Participant study:'][i]] == data['Did this voice agent ever make a mistake?'][i] for i in range(0,(len(data)))]]

Below graph shows boxplots with and without four observations above¶

In [102]:
for col in data.columns[2:30]:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(ncols = 2, figsize=(20,8), sharey= True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    ax[0].set_xlim([1, 3])
    ax[0].set_ylim([0, 10])
    ax[1].set_xlim([1, 3])
    ax[1].set_ylim([0, 10])
    data.boxplot(column=[col],by =data.columns[30],ax=ax[0], patch_artist=True)
    data_sanity_check.boxplot(column=[col],by =data_sanity_check.columns[30],ax=ax[1], patch_artist=True)

In [100]:
for col in data.columns[2:30]:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(ncols = 2, figsize=(20,8), sharey= True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    ax[0].set_xlim([1, 3])
    ax[0].set_ylim([0, 10])
    ax[1].set_xlim([1, 3])
    ax[1].set_ylim([0, 10])
    data.boxplot(column=[col],by =data.columns[1],ax=ax[0], patch_artist=True)
    data_sanity_check.boxplot(column=[col],by =data_sanity_check.columns[1],ax=ax[1], patch_artist=True)
